headline: BXP (BXP): Losses Worsen at 37.1% Rate, Profitability Forecast Within Three Years Challenges Bears
summary: BXP (BXP) posted another year of losses, with its net profit margin remaining negative and annual losses growing at an average rate of 37.1% over the past five years. Still, earnings are forecast to climb at a robust 44.86% per year, and the company is projected to become profitable within the next three years. Revenue is expected to grow by 2.1% annually, trailing the wider US market’s forecast of 10.2% a year. With notable risks still in play and a balance between near-term losses and...
